## Program 7: Ansible

### PART A — Install WSL and Ubuntu

**In Windows search bar:**
```
Windows features on or off
→ Check: Windows Subsystem for Linux
→ Click OK
→ Click Restart now
```

**After restart, open CMD as Administrator:**
```
wsl --list --online
wsl --install --distribution Ubuntu-24.04
```

**After installation:**
```
wsl
```
```
Create username: itishree (or your name)
New password: (type password - nothing shows, that is normal)
Retype password:
```

---

### PART B — Install Ansible

**Inside Ubuntu terminal:**
```
sudo apt update
sudo apt install ansible -y
ansible --version
```

---

### PART C — Create Project and Files

```
mkdir ansible-localhost
cd ansible-localhost
```

**Create inventory file:**
```
nano hosts.ini
```
Type:
```
[local]
localhost ansible_connection=local
```
CTRL+O → Enter → CTRL+X

**Test connection:**
```
ansible -i hosts.ini all -m ping
```
Should see: `SUCCESS` and `"ping": "pong"`

**Create HTML file:**
```
nano index.html
```
Type:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Custom Nginx Page</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello from Ansible!</h1>
    <p>This is a custom web page deployed using Ansible!</p>
</body>
</html>
```
CTRL+O → Enter → CTRL+X

**Create playbook:**
```
nano ansible.yml
```
Type:
```yaml
---
- name: Install and run nginx on localhost
  hosts: localhost
  become: yes
  tasks:
    - name: Install nginx
      apt:
        name: nginx
        state: present
        update_cache: yes
    - name: Copy custom index.html
      copy:
        src: index.html
        dest: /var/www/html/index.html
        owner: www-data
        group: www-data
        mode: '0644'
    - name: Start nginx service
      service:
        name: nginx
        state: started
        enabled: yes
```
CTRL+O → Enter → CTRL+X

**Verify files exist:**
```
ls
```
Should see: `ansible.yml  hosts.ini  index.html`

**Run playbook:**
```
ansible-playbook -i hosts.ini ansible.yml
```
Enter password when asked.
Should see: `failed=0`

**Verify in browser:**
Open `http://localhost`
Should see: **Hello from Ansible!**

